    "Challenges of conflict of interest or 'AI loyalty'.",
    "The concept of conflict of interest, or 'AI loyalty' (Aguirre et al., 2021) in educational institutions is largely absent in the current body of literature.",
    "For whom do AI systems work?",
    "Is it the students, schools, the education system, commercial players (e.g., AI edtech companies), or politicians?",
    "The question is not necessarily about the ethics of the technology itself, but rather about the ethics of the decision makers leading the companies behind AI's development, implementation, and use (Holmes et al., 2022)."
